- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with computability and complexity, which are fundamental concepts in logic and theoretical computer science. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the power of categories compared to Turing machines, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper deals with categorical structures, which are often studied in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the ability of categories to solve problems in the arithmetic hierarchy, which is related to information theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the construction of functions and functors, which are relevant to programming language theory.
